cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MM 

This paper proposes a visual tracking framework that utilizes a fully convolutional network (FCN) for parallel classification and regression. The paper focuses on computer vision and machine learning techniques for object tracking, which suggests that cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The use of FCN also indicates that the paper may fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper's focus on tracking objects suggests that it may also belong to cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
